# Success Criteria

The finished project should feel like something maintained by an experienced backend engineer.

It should be:

* easy to read
* easy to extend
* easy to debug
* easy to review

The workflow YAML should act as an orchestrator.

The Bash script should contain clean, well-organized production-quality logic.

Avoid both under-engineering and over-engineering.

Choose the simplest design that remains maintainable for the foreseeable future.
